<Base title="Apparently Small Significance of Puddles — Michalina Sablik">
  <div class="container page-content">
    <h1>Apparently Small Significance of Puddles</h1>
    <p class="exhibition-detail-venue">Art Walk Gallery, Warsaw | 2023</p>
    <div class="exhibition-detail-body">
      <p>Showcases the results of a year-long artistic research project centered on ephemeral urban water reservoirs. The two visual artists employed various artistic and scientific methods in their study of the "street holes" and water anomalies, inventing what they call a quasi-science to document puddle phenomena. Combines poetry, humour and the absurd with a serious study of hydro-ecological issues and the life of non-human beings in urban space. Features space-like, metal capsules, reminiscent of the history of cosmonautics in the 20th century. Introduces the fictional discipline of "puddlelogy."</p>
    </div>
    <div class="exhibition-detail-credits">
      <p><strong>Artists:</strong> Magdalena Lazar, Piotr Urbaniec</p>
    </div>
    <div class="exhibition-gallery" style="margin-top: 2.5rem; display: grid; gap: 1rem;">
